org.wikidata.wdtk.storage.dbquery

Class TripleTrie

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wikidata.wdtk.storage.dbquery.TripleTrie
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TrieIterable

    public class TripleTrie
extends Object
implements TrieIterable
    Data structure for storing a trie of integer sequences of equal length. The object requires data to be inserted in the natural order of the trie, and is therefore not suitable for modifications (hence the name). The advantage is that it can use very compact representations in memory.

    The first level of the trie is stored as a list of pointers to lower level data. The data in lower levels is linearized in int[] arrays.

    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch
